    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending operating envelope",
      "description": "Screw outer diameter: 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Rod diameter: 5.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Applied axial compressive load range: 0–2500 N. Crosshead displacement rate: 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min. Test block UHMWPE fixture per ASTM F1717 geometry; block slot depth 12.7 mm ± 0.3 mm. Ambient temperature: 20–25 °C. All constructs assembled with torque 8 Nm ± 0.5 Nm. Displacement monitored to 40 mm maximum. Validation dataset densely covers the full envelope: 11 constructs span both laboratories at the nominal load ramp, fixture geometry, and assembly torque specified."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw static compression-bending applicability",
      "description": "Model applicability is restricted to non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs with outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm assembled to titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) 5.5 mm rods. Loading mode is quasi-static axial compression-bending per ASTM F1717 only; dynamic fatigue, torsion, and cannulated variants are explicitly out of scope. Bone analog blocks must conform to ASTM F1717 UHMWPE specification. Constructs with accessory cross-links or offset connectors are excluded."
    }
  },
